title: PowerMac Perferred
description:
This preferred collection is a selection of hundreds of PowerMac native software from around the Internet. Use native utilities, interfaces, games, editors, communication applications and more.

Apple introduced the PowerPC, whose processor runs much faster than the 68K chips. Software written for the 68k machines can run on a PowerPC machine, but not at an increased speed. Software that is written to take advantage of the speed your PowerMac is called 'native' software. A program labeled 'fat' will run on a PowerPC while taking advantage of it's speed or on a 68k
